[00:44.69]'Would a later train get you to work on time?' asked the inspector.|“晚一点的火车能让你准时到达工作地点吗？”检查员问道。
[00:51.08]'I suppose it would, but I never catch a later train.'|“我想应该是这样的，但我从来都赶不上晚点的火车。”
[00:57.15]'At what time did you arrive at the station?'|你什么时候到达车站的？
[01:02.05]'At ten to eight. I bought a paper and waited for the train.'|八点十分的时候，我买了一张报纸，然后等待火车的到来。
[01:08.08]'And you didn't notice anything unusual?'|“那你没有注意到任何异常的情况吗？”
[01:13.13]'Of course not.'|“当然不会。”
[01:15.68]'I suggest,' said the inspector,' that you are not telling the truth.|“我认为，”检查员说，“你并没有说实话。”
[01:22.98]I suggest that you did not catch the 8 o'clock train,|我认为你可能没有赶上8点的火车。
[01:27.84]but that you caught the 8.25 which would still get you to work on time.|不过你赶上了8点25分的班车，这样仍然可以准时到达工作地点。
[01:34.87]You see, on the morning of the murder, the 8 o'clock train did not run at all.|你知道吗，在谋杀案发生的那个早晨，8点的火车根本就没有运行。
